==Old English==
===Etymology===
From unstressed Germanic prefix ''*ga-''.  Cognate with Old Saxon [[gi-]] (Dutch ''ge-''), Old High German [[ga-]] (German ''ge-''), Old Norse [[g-]], Gothic [[𐌲𐌰-]].

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/je/ or /jə/}}

===Prefix===
'''ġe-'''
# as an [[intensifier]] of verbs
# forming nouns or adjectives of [[association]] or [[similarity]]
# forming nouns and verbs with the sense of ‘result’ or ‘process’
# forming [[past participle|past participles]] or participle adjectives from verbs

===Descendents===
*Middle English [[y-]], [[i-]]

